Package: ATCodeR
Type: Package
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2024-11-05
Imports: tidyr, tidyverse, quanteda
Title: A dictionary-based R-tool to standardize medication free-text into ATC Codes
Author: Isabel Schnorr and Daniel Maier
Maintainer: Isabel Schnorr <i.schnorr@med.uni-frankfurt.de>
Description: Using a dictionary-based approach, the R-tool converts free-text medication  data into structured and standardized ATC codes. The resulting output is a structured data  frame containing columns for antineoplastic substances, other medications, and  supplementary information
License: The ATC dictionary is derived from WidO (https://www.wido.de/publikationen-produkte/analytik/arzneimittel-klassifikation/)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
StagedInstall: no
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
